4th annual international women's day breakfast the clayman institute for gender research skip to main content standford university the clayman institute for gender research the clayman institute for gender research home programs news strategic focus events about research fellowships library media center event information date & time march 1 2012 8 15am location you are here home events 4th annual international women's day breakfast 4th annual international women's day breakfast description in honor of international women's day women thrive worldwide along with honorary co chairs senator john kerry representative ted poe and representative jan schakowsky will be hosting a breakfast on capitol hill actor and activist maria bello fgm activist edna adan ismail and other distinguished panelists will host an event on capitol hill to discuss how we can work together to end violence against women across the globe women thrive worldwide a leading nonprofit organization advocating for policy change in the us and internationally so that women are granted the same opportunities as men and have the necessary tools to lift their entire community out of poverty please note this event is by invitation only but all are welcome to watch live so please bookmark the link to the webcast found here and be sure to tune in on march 1st at 8 30 am est or click through and have the website send you a reminder the day of women thrive worldwide also invites you to tweet along they will be using the hashtag noneinthree please feel free to use it while tweeting about the event or simply about gender based violence in general if you are interested in participating or hosting a dialogue in honor of international women's day this year or if you have any questions please feel free to contact maegan rees at mrees womenthrive org donate make a donation social links facebook twitter youtube scribd contact serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 8640 map 650 723 1994 gender email stanford edu
